    <br />

    <h2>What methods of payment can I use?</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:square;">
    <li><p>The PayPal system accepts all major credit cards.</p></li>
    </ul>
    <br />

    <h2>I can’t find my tickets / Can I reprint my tickets?</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:square;">
    <li><p>When you purchased your tickets, an email was sent to you that included a printable PDF of your tickets. You can reprint your tickets from that email at any time. If you did not save the PDF of your tickets to your computer, and you lose the email, you can request that the tickets be <a href="/resend_tickets"><b>resent</b></a> to you. Some events are free and do not require tickets. </p></li>
    </ul>
    <br />

    <h2>How do I get more information about the event I'm attending?</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:square;">
    <li><p>Eventastic doesn't actually organize the events on our site, so the best way to get your questions answered is to contact the Event Organizer. Go to the event listing and look for the Event Organizer’s contact information. If the Event Organizer has not listed their contact information, send an email to support@eventastic.com and we’ll connect you.  </p></li>
    </ul>
    <br />

    <h2>Can I obtain a refund or exchange once I’ve purchased my tickets?</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:square;">
    <li><p>Refunds and exchanges are the responsibility of the Event Organizer. It is the responsibility of the Event Organizer to communicate the refund policy and to issue refunds to Buyers via the Site or otherwise. All communications or disputes regarding refunds are between the Organizer and Buyer. Eventastic/Giftopia is not responsible or liable in any way for refunds, errors in issuing refunds, or lack of refunds in connection with the Services. </p></li>
    </ul>
    <br />

    <p><a href="/contact"><b>Can't find what you're looking for?  Ask us and someone from the Eventastic team will get back to you</b></a></p>

